<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Delheru on 03-22-2002 10:02 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Well hello there Gorian.. if Siren is who I think they are, their experience at the high end game is quite significantly vaster than yours.

Guess I'll lay down my l33t credits too since you question them if not ranked:
Lvl 60 clerics with about double everything you in gear.
Lead serverfirst new CT, NToV clear, Lendi, ST warder, AoW, Tunare, Ssra mobs, Burrower ring etc etc

So lets see about your assesment about what people do on raids.
 [QUOTE]
Shaman: Buffs Malo Slow Nukes Dots
Chanter: buffs tash slow Manasieve
Mages: Summons CoH Nukes Modrods pets DS
Clerics: Res's Buffs heals
Druids: DS nukes Dots ports snare heals buffs
Necros: LTs buffs dots pet Mana
Wizard: Ports Snares Nukes
[/QUOTE]

You aren't playing your cleric real well then.. first of all almost all the activities you list here require reasonable resists. LOL@snares of all things. So lets assume three "types" of encounter: (gonna adjust your list for them.. ports are also something that only twinks do anyway so won't even bother listing)

1. highly resistant to almost everything.. AoW, Tunare come to mind.
Shaman: buffs, malo  (notice malo can be cast by ONE shaman only, and once or max twice at that)
Chanter: buffs, maybe charming (hah again pretty weak, and while charming is pretty cool that often just isn't possible)
Mages: focus items, Modrods, pets, DS, nukes     (yeah list is relatively long, but only covering the problems of each item)
Clerics: Res's Buffs heals groupheals
Druids: DS nukes (both weak)
Necros: pet Mana (lol)
Wizard: Nukes

To me looks like clerics come off as by far most versatile here.

2. Not quite so resistant, but immune to attack speed changes. Like for example Tormax etc.

Shaman: Buffs Malo Nukes Dots (dots don't stack though)
Chanter: buffs tash charm
Mages: Summons Nukes Modrods pets DS
Clerics: Res's Buffs heals groupheals mok mor nukes
Druids: DS nukes Dots
Necros: LTs dots pet Mana
Wizard: Nukes

3. Wimpy "we suck all spells cast at us" mobs like Arch Lich.

Shaman: Buffs Malo Slow Nukes Dots
Chanter: buffs tash slowMages: Summons CoH Nukes Modrods pets DS
Clerics: Res's Buffs heals mok mor nukes groupheals
Druids: DS nukes Dots snare
Necros: LTs dots pet Mana
Wizard: Snares Nukes


Dunno looks to me like clerics are very well off, with wizards coming out as the least versatile, and druids and necros coming out looking bit ****ty.

-- Delheru Tanreall
